.TH "disk_stack_limits" 9 "disk_stack_limits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
disk_stack_limits \- adjust queue limits for stacked drivers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" disk_stack_limits
.BI "(struct gendisk *disk "  ","
.BI "struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "sector_t offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "disk" 12
MD/DM gendisk (top)
.IP "bdev" 12
the underlying block device (bottom)
.IP "offset" 12
offset to beginning of data within component device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Merges the limits for a top level gendisk and a bottom level
block_device.
